    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <fw type="letterhead" place="top-left" corresp="#Grayshott">
                    <dateline>
                        <name type="place" ref="#Grayshott">
                            <p>Telegrams:</p>
                            <p>Grayshott</p>
                        </name>
                    </dateline>
                </fw>
                <fw type="letterhead" place="top-right">
                    <dateline>
                        <name type="place" ref="#Hinhead">
                            <p>Undershaw,</p>
                            <p>Hinhead,</p>
                            <p>Haslemere.</p>
                        </name>
                    </dateline>
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Very many thanks for your kind letter. Since I wrote in The Times I have received much help from the Germans in England which I shall acknowledge when I write again.</p>
                <p>I should be delighted to answer any question of Professor <persName ref="#herrlich">Herrlich</persName>, but I don't know what I can add much to what I have said in the book. I was glad to see about the Eloff correction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With all thanks to your two friends and yourself.</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="#ACD">A. Conan Doyle</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <note>
                    <persName ref="#bloch">Bloch of Pottsdammer Strasse, Berlin</persName> is the German publisher in case you want copies.</note>
            </div>
        </body>
